                <section>
                    <h>dependents</h>
                    <section id="sgriobhadh-spec">
                        <h>specifier/object</h>
                        <p>The object of the verb <g>sgrìobh</g> appears as the specifier of the
                            derived (deverbal) noun.</p>
                        <p>Examples –<ul>
                                <li>older pedagogical examples – <xl
                                        id="sgriobhadh-spec-older-pedag">
                                        <li>
                                            <gd>Tha mo mhàthair a’ <m>sgrìobhadh litreach</m> gu
                                                m’athair a tha air falbh.</gd>
                                            <tr>My mother is writing a letter [lit. at a letter’s
                                                writing] to my father who is away.</tr>
                                            <ref text="621">td. 5</ref>
                                            <note>cf. <g>sgrìobh i litir</g>.</note>
                                        </li>
                                    </xl>
                                </li>
                            </ul></p>
                    </section>
                    <section id="sgriobhadh-complements">
                        <h>complements</h>
                        <p>Other complements of the verb remain as complements of the derived
                            noun.</p>
                        <p>Examples –<ul>
                                <li>older pedagogical examples – <xl
                                        id="sgriobhadh-comp-older-pedag">
                                        <li>
                                            <gd>Tha mo mhàthair a’ <m>sgrìobhadh</m> litreach <m>gu
                                                  m’athair</m> a tha air falbh.</gd>
                                            <tr>My mother is writing a letter [lit. at a letter’s
                                                writing] to my father who is away.</tr>
                                            <ref text="621">td. 5</ref>
                                            <note>cf. <g>sgrìobh i litir gu m’athair</g>.</note>
                                        </li>
                                    </xl>
                                </li>
                            </ul></p>
                    </section>
                </section>
                <section>
